AFAIK, the EvidenceResult has a validator so, correct me if I&#39;m wrong, when click on OK button in the popup the validations are runneed. So maybe a fail can happen and this logic is going to be executed allways, with and without errors.
To avoid that, add the following:
	if (Messages.getErrorMessages().isEmpty()) {
    		evidenceResultPersistenceService.updateEvidenceResultForAllSelectedLeavePlans(getEvidenceResult());
		selectedLeavePlanPersistenceService.updateEvidenceResultType(evidenceResult.getSelectedLeavePlan(),
		        evidenceResultService.calculateOverallEvidenceDecision(evidenceResult.getSelectedLeavePlan()));

    }

Then, the update will be only executed if there is no errors.

Add tests to verify it with and without errors.

You don&#39;t need to raise effectively a message, just mocked it:

		new Expectations(Messages.class) {
			{
				Messages.getErrorMessages().isEmpty();
				result = false;
			}
		};

Do the same for the true expectation.

